  <prompt>Read FR-12 + the Owner Q&amp;A on dispatch mechanism from spec.md, verify spaarkedev1 access via the Dataverse MCP, investigate the `sprk_playbookconsumer` entity built in chat-routing-redesign-r1 Phase 1R, and document whether the widget-as-consumer pattern can dispatch to `DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE`. Record the chosen dispatch path (Path A = sprk_playbookconsumer; Path B = direct AnalysisOrchestrationService with degenerate playbook) in `notes/decisions/030-dispatch-path.md`. Required before task 030 rewrites the wrapper.</prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. JPS playbook engine + BFF AI-orchestration researcher; able to read C# service code and map it to a Dataverse-data dispatch decision.</role>

  <goal>A written decision document at `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/notes/decisions/030-dispatch-path.md` that names the chosen dispatch path (A or B), cites the code evidence for the choice, and lists the structured payload shape `DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE` will accept. MCP access to spaarkedev1 verified.</goal>

