    <step order="4">Survey `DailyBriefingEndpoints.HandleNarrate` (current hardcoded implementation) to capture the request payload shape that the new playbook dispatch must accept.</step>
    <step order="5">Survey `AnalysisOrchestrationService` to capture the direct-invoke signature (Path B fallback).</step>
    <step order="6">Decide Path A (sprk_playbookconsumer) vs Path B (direct AnalysisOrchestrationService + degenerate playbook). Criteria: does sprk_playbookconsumer accept the daily-briefing payload shape without modification? Is the consumer→playbook mapping data-driven (no code change in BFF needed)?</step>
    <step order="7">Create directory `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/notes/decisions/` if it does not exist. Author `030-dispatch-path.md` containing: (a) decision (A or B), (b) cited code evidence (file:line refs), (c) proposed structured payload, (d) impact on task 030 wrapper rewrite.</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change this task's status to ✅.</step>
    <step order="9">If deviations from plan, document in projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/notes/.</step>
